ZH: 这个案件需要一位可靠的证人来提供证词。
EN: This case needs a reliable witness to provide testimony.

ZH: 她是这起车祸事故的唯一证人。
EN: She is the only witness to this car accident.

ZH: 他不愿意在法庭上作证人。
EN: He is unwilling to testify as a witness in court.

ZH: 案发时，他正在场景附近，成为了一个重要证人。
EN: He was near the scene when the incident occurred, becoming an important witness.

ZH: 持枪抢劫的嫌疑犯被逮捕是因为有多位目击证人。
EN: The suspect in the armed robbery was arrested due to multiple eyewitnesses.

ZH: 这名证人拥有关键的证据来证明被告的罪行。
EN: This witness possesses crucial evidence to prove the defendant's guilt.

ZH: 法庭要求所有证人作证前先宣誓。
EN: The court demands that all witnesses take an oath before testifying.

ZH: 他在证人席上坐得笔直，目光坚定。
EN: He sits upright in the witness stand, with a determined gaze.

ZH: 证人应当按实际情况回答问题，不能隐瞒真相。
EN: Witnesses should answer questions based on the actual situation and not conceal the truth.

ZH: 法庭上的证人受到法官和律师的询问。
EN: The witnesses in the court are subjected to questioning by the judge and lawyers.

ZH: 这位证人的证词与其他证人的版本不相符。
EN: The testimony of this witness does not match the accounts of other witnesses.

ZH: 他是检察官的证人之一，将提供重要线索。
EN: He is one of the prosecutor's witnesses and will provide crucial clues.

ZH: 这名证人的口供被认定为不可靠的证据。
EN: The testimony of this witness is deemed unreliable evidence.

ZH: 陪审团认为这位证人的证言不可靠。
EN: The jury considers the witness's testimony to be unreliable.

ZH: 证人回忆起案发现场的细节，帮助了警方的调查。
EN: The witness recalls details of the crime scene, aiding the police investigation.

ZH: 这位证人被要求提供手写笔迹鉴定样本。
EN: This witness is asked to provide a handwriting sample for identification.

ZH: 一位匿名证人向警方提供了关键线索。
EN: An anonymous witness provides crucial information to the police.

ZH: 这个案件的许多证人都拒绝接受采访。
EN: Many witnesses in this case refuse to be interviewed.

ZH: 这个法庭开庭时，证人全部到场。
EN: All witnesses are present when this court is in session.

ZH: 证人的证词对被告的判决有着重要的影响。
EN: The testimony of the witness has a significant impact on the defendant's verdict.
